{
  "text": "Methods for counting robots have been proposed in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Brambilla et al. [CITATION_3] use an algorithm similar to firefly signalling. The algorithm counts the number of nearby robots that are signalling during a period of time. Ding and Hamann [CITATION_4] use an algorithm that counts the number of locally connected robots and causes them to self-organize into two different areas based on their assigned colors. The robots have unique IDs, and exchange these IDs via pair-wise communication until all robots within communication range share the same set of IDs.",
  "citation_candidates": [
